msgid "Choosing the appropriate shape for your *Area* light will enhance the believability of your scene. For example, you may have an indoor scene and would like to simulate light entering through a window. You could place a *Rectangular* area lamp in a window (vertical) or from neons (horizontal) with proper ratio for *Size X* and *Size Y*. For the simulation of the light emitted by a TV screen, a vertical *Square* area lamp would be better in most cases."
